        "author_association": "OWNER",
        "body": "Visual History's popup is just html injected into the page, which Google views as \"reading and changing all the data on websites you visit\". That warning is even triggered whenever there's a content script that matches all [all urls](https://developer.chrome.com/extensions/permission_warnings#warnings), regardless of whether the extension actually uses it or not.\n\nI agree that it's misleadingly broad, which is one of the reasons this is open-source.\n\nA possible alternative would be using the [activeTabs](https://developer.chrome.com/extensions/activeTab) permissions, but I think that wouldn't let the extension track tab info unless the user generate some request on that page. I'll look into it.\n"
    },
