        "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
        "body": "Unfortunately, `history` doesn't provide enough information to provide a tree structure of a user's browsing history. For a given page, the extension needs to know the parent page (that is, which site the user was on when they went to the next page). Because a `history` only provides a chronologically linear list of sites (which this extension aims to enhance), there's no way to gather that information from `history` alone.\n"
    },
